				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The fact that some games have battery-backed SRAM doesn't mean that they have to use it exclusively for saving. I'm pretty sure most games use it mainly as extra RAM, for level maps or similarly large data.
<br />
<br />Most of the time, 8KB is too much for save data, but since Nintendo already used 8KB RAM chips for CHR-RAM it was probably easier/cheaper for them to use the same chip than to go with something smaller.</div>

