						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">cartlemmy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Now, that sounds really cool. Would I go about developing it like normal WRAM?</div><br />No, FlashROM is very different from RAM. FlashROM would have to be used strictly for saving/restoring data, because it's slower to write to (you can't freely write to any address you want, you have to write to sectors or something) and they can be rewritten a limited number of times (the number is large, like several thousand times, but it's still limited).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">No extra parts needed because the PRG-ROM is the FlashROM.</div>
<br />I worry about that a bit. I fear that the program might crash and somehow end up overwriting parts of the program itself... Losing your saved data is already bad enough, but losing the actual game is much worse.</div>

