				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can use ROM, But that'd only be good for things that aren't updated every frame, more like 10 times a play or something small. Because if it saves AND uses the SRAM at the same time, the Flash would be pretty much useless and overkill. IMO, just sticking to the SRAM+Battery is better since it can double as a RAM. That's kinda the whole point of the RAM I'd think.
<br />
<br />
<br />Although, it'd be interesting to see a FlashROM in a cart too. Or do as I think was said some time ago, use s serial flash ROM and make a "memory card" that plugs into the expansion port/controller port and use that. That'd be far better IMO. More games can use it if they wanted, and it'd be cheaper than including a Flash ROM in every cart.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

